{
  "query": "What are the potential negative impacts on native vegetation of sowing grass seeds at high densities in the USA?",
  "relevant_summary": "According to studies conducted in the USA, sowing grass seeds at high densities can have several negative impacts on native vegetation. Action 3397 found that sowing grass seeds reduced native grass cover and reduced the abundance of native forb species and shrub species in studies conducted in the USA and Canada. The same action documented that sowing grass seeds reduced the abundance of grassland species and that species richness was lower than that found in nearby intact prairies in some studies. Action 3405 specifically examined higher density seeding and found that sowing grass seeds at a higher density reduced the cover of native grassland shrubs in a site comparison study in the USA. Additionally, Action 3397 found that three of four replicated studies in the USA and Canada showed that sowing grass seeds either reduced native grass cover or did not alter native grass density, indicating competitive effects on native grasses.",
  "action_ids": [
    "3397",
    "3405"
  ]
}

